The paper deals with secure computation on decentralized data markets, which involves privacy-preserving techniques for data analysis. This falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR) as well as databases (cs.DB). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques such as homomorphic encryption, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy concerns in sensitive datasets, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
